{"id":14881599,"mediaExerciseId":"5ad2d5df-51a9-4666-9d73-4eccd2bbcc6e","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"17","chapterTitle":"Dividends and Payout Policy","groupId":612429,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":602,"solutions":[{"id":5985146,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"This exercise requires us to determine the **ex-dividend price**. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Ex-dividend** is a stock state in which the shareholders are not entitled to receive any dividends, and stock prices no longer include the dividends. The ex-dividend price measures the stock price decrease as the stock goes ex-dividend. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":30,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/43c4622a56828ce532618b8ea3603417/lateximg_large.png","width":857},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/43c4622a56828ce532618b8ea3603417/lateximg.png","width":430}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Ex-dividend Price is computed as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Ex-dividend Price} &= \\text{Current Price} - {\\text{After Tax Dividend}}\\\\[1pt]\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/fce7a228795d792eefb01658714ff9c6/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/fce7a228795d792eefb01658714ff9c6/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's identify the given amounts in the problem:\n\n<center>\n\n| |Amounts | \n|--|:--:| \n|Dividends |$5.35| \n|Capital Gains Tax Rate|15% | \n| Stock Price|$74.20 | \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":97,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/0c1be50be22348224b5a22d698b669f9/lateximg_large.png","width":875},"regular":{"height":50,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/0c1be50be22348224b5a22d698b669f9/lateximg.png","width":437}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we compute the ex-dividend price, let's first Identify the after tax dividend using the equation below:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{After Tax Dividend} &= \\text{Dividend} \\times {\\text{(1 - Tax Rate)}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{\\$ 5.35} \\times {\\text{(1 - 15\\%)}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{\\$ 5.35} \\times {\\text{0.85}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\underline{\\underline{\\text{\\$ 4.55}}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/20e5238c0d546a22cdec3af7adc20f00/lateximg_large.png","width":1216},"regular":{"height":46,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/20e5238c0d546a22cdec3af7adc20f00/lateximg.png","width":609}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Now that we have computed the after tax dividend, we can now compute the ex-dividend price using the equation in step 3.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Ex-dividend Price} &= \\text{Current Price} - {\\text{After Tax Dividend}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\text{\\$ 74.20} - {\\text{\\$ 4.55}}\\\\[5pt]\n&= \\underline{\\underline{\\textbf{\\$ 69.65}}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nAs can be seen, the ex-dividend price of Ginder, Inc. is **$ 69.65**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":318,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/80c49845222b177332281e82bf8592a9/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":161,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/0f3b528aacaa125863ac2f65d0484ce1/80c49845222b177332281e82bf8592a9/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"2e8bde4c-e639-4f83-a8f7-7c3aaf8f5796","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881600,"exerciseName":"2","page":602,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a65b6593-64e0-4e6f-8515-47626c757c15","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-17-questions-and-problems-2-a65b6593-64e0-4e6f-8515-47626c757c15"},{"id":14881601,"exerciseName":"3","page":602,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"8dcd72e9-6e9b-4b23-8688-faceef5bc252","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-17-questions-and-problems-3-8dcd72e9-6e9b-4b23-8688-faceef5bc252"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881598,"exerciseName":"10","page":601,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1e4